    "attributes": {
        "action": "Do not extend Sunday Trading Hours for Retail",
        "additional_details": "Many big retailers have remained open during the pandemic, and the Government should not increase pressures on shop workers by extending opening hours on Sunday.\r\n\r\nCurrent hours can already be a strain on family life, and extending these would cause rota issues and mean more staff will need to work on Sunday.",
        "background": "The Government should not extend Sunday trading hours. We believe this would cause no overall increase in spending but would cause problems for already hard-working shop staff, who would have to change rotas and plan for additional opening times.",
